article:
'Dry River' may refer to:
* Dry River (Jamaica)
* Dry River (New Hampshire), in the United States
* Dry River (Crooked River), a river in Oregon
* Dry River (New South Wales), a river in Australia
* Dry River (Northern Territory)
* Dry River (Virginia), in the United States
* Dry River, New Zealand, a river in the North Island of New Zealand
* Dry river anarchist collective, an anarchist group and meeting place in
  Tucson, Arizona
* "Dry River", the hidden entrance to Gondolin, a location in the fiction of J.
  R. R. Tolkien
